ization step always produces the same final label.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior text explicitly scopes to normalization determinism for identical raw input, which is a single-function/object property with no required module boundary or I/O. Rejected Integration because no cross-module handoff is required by the behavior text. Rejected Agentic because it does not depend on real model output variation; input is fixed.","test_description":"Call normalization with the same raw response fixture repeatedly and assert identical normalized label each time.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"On repeated live API calls for the same document and taxonomy, the returned label remains consistent unless the provider response itself changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior requires repeated live model calls and checks consistency of model-produced labels over time; this depends on real LLM/API behavior and potential non-determinism. Mocked responses would always pass and hide true inconsistency. Rejected Workflow because this is repeated single-step classification calls, not a chained multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Against the real provider, run N repeated classifications for identical input/taxonomy, record provider responses/labels, and assert label stability when provider response content is unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.71,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Request construction enforces the configured token budget before dispatch (for example truncate/reject according to policy).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode is at local module boundary: tokenizer/budget policy + request-construction + dispatch gate. Unit tests of token math 