ic. Rejected System because behavior text does not require real HTTP timing semantics beyond simulated rate-limit responses. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness is infra control-flow around the call, not model decision quality or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Use a stub provider that returns rate-limit signal then success; assert module waits/backs off, retries expected times, and returns successful label instead of propagating immediate error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
